# coul/exclude correctness test (Step 4: pair_coul_exclude_omp verification)
# atom_style full provides per-atom charge + bond topology. The data file
# (data.coul_exclude_test) defines 216 four-atom linear chains (bond length
# 1.0, charges alternating +1/-1/+1/-1) connected via
# bond_style zero (no force/energy), purely to establish 1-2/1-3/1-4
# special-bond topology.
# special_bonds lj/coul values are all strictly between 0 and 1 so that
# 1-2, 1-3 and 1-4 pairs remain in the neighbor list with sbmask set and
# factor_coul = special_coul[sbmask]-1.0 != 0 for all three cases.
# cut_global=3.5 covers the 1-4 distance (3.0) within each chain.
# pair_style coul/exclude has no cutsq/itype/jtype dependence and is fully
# deterministic (no RNG), so standard/omp1/omp4 are expected bit-identical.

units           lj
atom_style      full
boundary        p p p

read_data       data.coul_exclude_test
